02:22.976 --> 02:25.677
Whoo-wee. That is awesome.

02:25.745 --> 02:27.979
This is ridiculous, this view.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.720
For myself and many others,

02:34.788 --> 02:36.722
San francisco isn't
just a place.

02:36.790 --> 02:38.957
It represents an ideal.

02:40.594 --> 02:42.828
From the beats
in the north beach.

02:42.896 --> 02:44.329
And the hippies
on the haight-ashbury.

02:44.331 --> 02:46.665
To the gay rights activists
in the castro.

02:46.733 --> 02:48.266
And the tech takeover today,

02:48.335 --> 02:50.268
This place has been
at the forefront.

02:50.337 --> 02:52.137
Of some seismic societal shifts.

02:52.205 --> 02:54.973
That have reshaped generations.

02:55.041 --> 02:57.342
San francisco,
you can't beat it, man.

02:57.410 --> 02:59.611
I'll tell you. It's
the cutting edge for culture.

02:59.680 --> 03:02.113
It's the place where
all the weirdos can go.

03:02.182 --> 03:03.582
And find each other.

03:03.650 --> 03:06.118
It has the hippies still.
It has mission still.

03:06.186 --> 03:07.886
It's got a amazing,
unique character.

03:07.954 --> 03:11.523
That's really not found
in any other city in the world.

03:11.591 --> 03:13.292
For me, san francisco symbolized.

03:13.360 --> 03:15.293
The cutting edge
of metal and punk.

03:15.362 --> 03:17.796
Bands like
operation ivy and primus.

03:17.864 --> 03:20.766
Could have only come out of
san francisco at that time.

03:20.834 --> 03:22.701
